Package parser

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddParser
    This class is a child class of the CommandParser.
    CommandParser
    This class is an abstract class that is the parent class for AddParser, EditParser and SearchParser.
    Constants
    This class contains all the constant regular expressions that the parser will use.
    DateParser
    This class focuses on breaking down a string for date into the relevant components it takes in a date input with varying degree of flexibility, in dd/mm/yy or number-month-year format.
    DateTimeParser
    This class is the facade class that hides the DateParser and TimeParser from the CommandParsers.
    EditParser
    This class is the child class of CommandParser.
    Parser
    This class takes in the user's input and processes it, identifying the command type and details of the command to exeucute.
    SearchParser
    This class is a child class of CommandParser.
    TimeParser
    This class's job is to identify the correct time from a user's string input.
